text: I hail this decision. I fought against PDAF, part of the folks in the Million People March, went on to form with many who felt PDAF was but the start of the fight, the #ScrapPork network, which also campaigned against executive port, especially DAP.  http://news.abs-cbn.com/news/06/20/18/ombudsman-indicts-ex-president-aquino-over-dap …

#ScrapPork believed it wasn’t enough to demand justice for those who diverted money from PDAF, not enough to win an SC victory against PDAF. Our slogan was Lahat #DAPatManagot. DAP took away funds from programs already approved by Congress to give to favored allies of Aquino.

DAP was presented as a devt tool. But patronage and cooperation were its main goals. I also remember Mr Aquino attacking the Supreme Court for its stand on DAP, which he used in the Corona impeachment.
Let the chips fall where they should. Lahat #DAPatmanagot

Opposition to Mr Duterte should not make one blind to the grave abuse of power by Mr Aquino. Fighting Duterte’s abuses does not mean sweeping the dirt of the past into some hidden corner. Lahat #DAPatmanagot

But let me note that the Duterte regime continues to practice patronage politics via the pork barrel, using the same creative practices of the Aquino govt. Some companions in the fight against pork swiftly turned around and urged more of the same to keep Congress tame.
This is why I have such high respect for Judy Taguiwalo. She took on Congress on the issue of pork, even knowing it meant risking her confirmation.
The fight against pork must continue. True,  the fight for basic human rights must come first but it is time to revisit pork — under this regime.
